<br>
Verant designed the Bazaar with stalls All throughout the zone.  However, it seems everyone is crowding around the stalls by the Banks. This makes a lot of people in a small area and that makes lots of lag as you run passed this huge crowd.  (unfortunately this makes banking bad as well since they are crowded by the banks).  Feel free to spread out people!!!   There are a number of other stalls always seemingly EMPTY!!  <br>
<br>
Also, you really don't have to actually Browse by moving around your character.  You can use the Bazaar search window  (&quot;/bazaar&quot;) to look up any specific item or any group of items that might be of interest to your character.  The items stats and the merchant selling it along with his price are all listed in this window.  You can sit in one place and browse the WHOLE bazaar's list of items for sale.  This also allows you to see who has the best price, if more then one person happens to have the items for sale.<br>
<br>
Its true also, if you turn off some of the new models it does improve your Lag problems.  As well as the clipping plane.  My advice though would be for those with the worst lag, simply enter the zone ONLY to buy and sell, and head for the back of the bazaar away from the banks to set up shop and browse with the Bazaar Search Window. <p>Perimen Chath`Elghinn <BR>
Wizard of the Spurned<BR>
